frameDefinitions: The existence of a State_of_affairs is sufficient reason for taking an Action .
This scenario describes a series of Events, associated with a single Participant, i.e., the history of the Participant.
A Question about the reason or cause of a known State_of_affairs is presented as being answered by the existence of a particular Fact.
A Goal has a Source from which it has gotten a Theme.
An Agent is responsible for having intentionally performed an Act or for being the or a primary instigator behind the Act.

The answer to one open question, the Outcome, is dictated (partially or completely) by the answer to another open question, the Determinant, i.e. if the answer to the Determinant is known, the answer to the Outcome can be predicted.
frameExamples: The underwater sequences <t>warrant</t> the price of the admission alone.
We've been worried about our recent hire's <t><fex name='Events'>history</fex></t> of deceiving employers.
Ruby's orange vest marked with the words 'service dog' <t>accounts</t> for why the 3-year-old goes along.
she is my friend...not to mention my <t>source</t> for French madeleines!
It has been determined that a relatively unknown terrorist group is <t>responsible</t> for the recent attacks.
Economic policy is partially a <t>function</t> of cultural values.
listRoleDefinitions: An Eventuality or an Entity that is taken to constitute sufficient reason for taking another <fen>Action</fen>.
An <fen>Action</fen> that is taken to be justifiable given the <fen>State_of_Affairs</fen>.

The <fen>Participant</fen> is either an active participant in all of the <fen>Events</fen> (e.g., Agent or Patient), or is more peripherally associated with the <fen>Events</fen> (e.g., Location or Topic).
The <fen>Events</fen> which the <fen>Participant</fen> is a part of. This role is used to mark the frame-evoking element.
A <fen>Fact</fen> which can be connected by a chain of reasoning to the <fen>State_of_affairs</fen>.
A <fen>Fact</fen> whose cause is under consideration.
An open proposition concerning the cause of the <fen>State_of_affairs</fen>.
The abstact or concrete thing acquired by the <fen>Goal</fen> from the <fen>Source</fen>.
A concrete or abstract entity from which the <fen>Goal</fen> has gotten the <fen>Theme</fen>.
An entity or individual that has acquired a <fen>Theme</fen> from the <fen>Source</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Act</fen> that the <fen>Agent</fen> performs intentionally.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> acts intentionally.
This role identifies the place where the intentional act occurs.
An open question that is (to some degree) predictable from the Determinant.
An open question that determines the <fen>Outcome</fen>.
